title: Cramer's game plan: Friday's rebound is something to celebrate going into next week
text: Jim Cramer takes a look at the week ahead and talks about what earnings reports he will be watching.

title: One data point won't determine economic weakness, says expert
text: Kate Moore, BlackRock chief equity strategist, and Kourtney Gibson, president of Loop Capital join the "Fast Money Halftime Report" panel to discuss a weak jobs number and its effects on the market.

title: Stifel economist sees positive, slower US growth for 2019
text: Lindsey Piegza, Stifel chief economist, joins 'Squawk Alley' to discuss the state of the U.S. economy after February's weak jobs report.

title: SpaceX's Crew Dragon returns home with a splash
text: After successfully returning to Earth, SpaceX's Crew Dragon vehicle gets one step closer to carrying astronauts into space.

title: Jim Cramer on Boardroom diversity
text: Jim Cramer and Katherine Ross on the floor of the NYSE.

title: China ETFs outperform broader market â€” Here are the ones to watch
text: CNBC's Bob Pisani reports on the China ETFs seeing an outperformance despite the U.S.-China trade war tensions.

title: Watch CNBC's full interview with Larry Kudlow following weak jobs data
text: White House economic advisor Larry Kudlow joins "Squawk on the Street" for the first White House reaction to the February jobs report. They also discuss productivity numbers, the overall economy and Huawei's decision to sue the U.S. government.

title: SpaceX completes historic Crew Dragon test flight for NASA with splashdown in the Atlantic Ocean
text: SpaceX splashed its Crew Dragon capsule into the Atlantic Ocean safely on Friday morning, completing the company's test flight to the International Space Station.
